{"questionId":"21317","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A piece of candy is made in the shape of a solid hemisphere. The radius of the hemisphere&nbsp;is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>mm</mtext></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/a386e91857d4ba1b2288b75fbf55ecbd7bc192a3.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the <strong>total</strong> surface area of one piece of candy.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>6</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>6</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>6</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)(A1)(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for use of surface area of a sphere formula (or curved surface area of a hemisphere), <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for substituting correct values into hemisphere formula, <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for adding the area of the circle.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>339</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mtext>mm</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>108</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>339</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>292</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21317","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ1.3a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-